My first Met Gala was in 2015: I was invited by @calvinklein and I was so scared to be there. 
2015 was a very depressing time of my life: I was living in Los Angeles, was in a relationship that wasn’t working, I felt so alone and professionally in cage, while other people were making most of my decisions. 
Met Gala was still amazing, but if I think of that year I can only think “Good job Chiara for getting out of that time of your life, creating your own rules and becoming your boss, making your OWN decisions and creating the family you’ve always dreamt of” 
If 2015 Chiara could see 2022 Chiara I think she would cry with happiness, and this is what this Met Gala means to me: hand in hand with my husband, happy and proud. 
We all deserve to feel this way 💖

@nespresso family invited me to Mexico to meet its female coffee farmers, like Pastora Caballero that you see in these pictures with me ☺️ She is a role model in her community and is one of the first women here in Veracruz to become financially and socially independent thanks to her work harvesting coffee 🌱☕️ we discovered we have a lot in common: we are both entrepreneurs, moms and we both love coffee 💘 @nespresso.mx #NespressoxChiaraFerragni #adv

The first photo was taken last night, while the second one was shot in January 2020, right before a job in Mexico (like today). 
Everytime I leave for work and especially when I travel far from my kids I feel so lucky and broken at the same time. Lucky because I created the job of my dreams, I’m the ceo of my companies and this is such a rare case in a world full of men being in power. 
At the same time being far from them, physically far from them, breaks my heart. I miss their smell, touch and hugs. I’m so lucky to be their mama and I hope they grow being proud of what I’m building for them ❤️

For the most part of my teenage/adult life my biggest physical insecurity has been my skin: I’ve always had breakouts/acne and showing my skin when it was inflammed was very triggering for me. 
In the past 6 years my skin has changed and got so much better: what really helped me was balancing my hormones with inositol (totally natural), live a happier life and not think about it too much. Every once in a while I get breakouts, and It’s totally ok and I made peace with the situation. 
The day we were finally discharged from the hospital I had a very bad rash on the right part of my chin: I blame it on my hormones + obviously super high stress level. I could have avoided talking about it and showing it but then I was thinking.. Why should I not talk about it? We have to normalize bad skin days too, and not having the pressure to ever feel perfect 🙏🏻

Last Saturday It was Leone’s 4th birthday. We had organized a big party with all of his classmates and friends since he hadn’t really celebrated the past two years due to the pandemic, but we had to change it the day before: daddy had to go through surgery on Tuesday and It was important not to get covid before that (so not so many people involved).
So we only had his five best friends come, and family. 
Our mood wasn’t the most festive but It ended up being a great party for our little one 💖 Grateful for these memories 🙏🏻

This was pretty much our week after Fede’s diagnosis and leading up to his surgery: we took some time off social media, spent as much time as possible with the kids, went for a lot of visits and exams, went for walks, had gelato sitting on a bench, spent some time with his closest friends, recorded some music (he did and I listened), slept with Leo in our bed (he usually sleeps in his room) and celebrated his 4th birthday. 
Most of this time felt like a blur: it was like time had stopped and I was scared like never before in my life that something bad could have happened. 
Thanks life for turning things around for the best 🙏🏻🤞🏻🙏🏻

This pic was taken on Monday afternoon at the hospital, the day before his pancreas delicate surgery. 
We were scared for everything: his diagnosis, his surgery, his recovery, our life and the fiture of our family. 
The surgery on Tuesday went well, and he’s now recovering and hopefully this will only be a bad memory that taught us, once again, the importance of enjoying life to the fullest, everyday 🙏🏻 
Thanks to all the people who made us feel their love, reached out and said a prayer for us, it gave us a lot of strenght 🙏🏻

Ho riso, ho pianto, ma sopratutto ho imparato molto dalle storie d’amore e di vita di @loredane_tshilombo @saralapignola @mehths @chiarapierii @nickcerioni @leandroemede . Sono loro i protagonisti assoluti dell’iniziativa #LoveFiercely che ho voluto in supporto ad @cigarcigaymilano e che in questo video si raccontano. Sono loro i protagonisti, le voci, le anime belle che spero possano essere d’esempio a noi tutti e simbolo di un cambiamento radicale nella società dove voglio essere orgogliosa di vivere e crescere la mia famiglia. Un grazie speciale anche a @paoloarmelli , lui è stato la guida di questo racconto schietto ed emozionante. Un grazie a tutte le persone del mio team che ogni giorno si battono per portare alla luce progetti come questo @fabiomariadamato filippoinnocenti @luisa_loz @azzurragentile @chiaradadalt @fabionu_ perché il nostro non è solo un lavoro di squadra ma una comunione di valori ❤️

Ho a lungo pensato a cosa scrivere e come scriverlo per non essere fraintesa e non permettere di strumentalizzare il messaggio di amore in cui credo da sempre e con cui oggi voglio fare un passo ulteriore, personale e concreto. Love Fiercely per me non è solo il motto del mio percorso di essere umano, ma un credo da condividere con tutti e un ideale per il quale battersi. Amare con fierezza, amare come vuoi e chi vuoi è il significato di tutto quello che ha spinto le mie scelte, sempre, tutto quello in cui ho sempre creduto, tutto quello che oggi mi permette di essere la persona innamorata delle della mia vita e di chi la popola. Con la campagna #LoveFiercely che ho voluto in supporto ad @cigarcigaymilano oggi voglio dire a tutti di amare se stessi prima di tutto, perché solo cosí ci si sente liberi di amare come e chi si vuole. Io nella mia vita l’ho fatto, ho amato indipendentemente dal genere, senza farmi costringere dalle etichette che gli altri volevano darmi e lo stesso hanno fatto @loredane_tshilombo e @saralapignola, @nickcerioni e @leandroemede, @mehths e @chiarapierii.  La mia storia e le storie di queste tre coppie che stimo spero possano essere di esempio per tutti , perché amare in maniera pura è sempre la scelta più giusta che ognuno di noi può fare. Grazie a questa iniziativa e ad una mia donazione personale supporteremo il progetto Scuola di @cigarcigaymilano: andremo nelle scuole di Milano e provincia per raccontare queste storie d'amore e sensibilizzare i giovanissimi sulle tematiche del bullismo. Adesso è il tuo turno, raccontami la tua storia di amore fiero taggami e utilizza #LoveFiercely così io possa vederla 💖

My speech last night receiving GQ Woman of the Year Award 🙏🏻
“I am so proud to receive this award today after a very challenging year and a half we all have experienced. 
What everyone, me included, has tried to do this year was to help the community, and I am not talking about social media community only, but also the real community out there in the world. 
One year and half today my husband and I raised 5 milion euros and we built a new intensive care unit of a hospital in Milan, my hometown, for the Covid emergency and we did it in just 2 weeks, which is pretty incredible. 
We also tried to connect fabric producers and all the clothing companies to make face masks for the hospitals of our country. 
For the first time, in a globalised world, we started to think local. 
Wa wanted to support people all all over the world using our voices and media influence by helping them to connect and concretely help each other.
This is the reason why today I am so proud to receive this award. 
Because I know that I am more than just a pretty face giving fashion advices and I hope I demonstrated that change can come from anyone. Everyone can make the difference. Everyone, little by little and fighting every day, can create a positive change. 
For this reason I want to dedicate this award to all the women, and human beings, that are brave enough to believe in the power of people.
Thank you everyone 🙏🏻”

12 years ago when I started my career I was looking at Vogue Italia, and at the editor-in-chief of the time, as a world far away from mine.
To me it was a little circle of creative people to look up to, especially since I was only at the beginning of this crazy journey and I didn’t have any connections. The first fashion shows I was invited to I had a standing invitation, from which you can’t see most of the show, while the important people were seated front row.
Today, being on the cover of Vogue Italia @vogueitalia is a goal that makes feel proud of that little girl that started her little blog in 2009. It’s a dream that came true after a lot of sacrifice and hard work. 
For this special cover I really want to thank @franragazzi and all the young and enthusiastic team behind this work 🙏 Thanks to the photographer duo @scandebergs and to the incredible sense of fashion of @poppykain 💪 This is not my first Vogue cover but it is one of the most precious ones ❤️ 
The cover will hit the newsstands on Thursday 7th October 🥰

“Giuro mi fai venire voglia di futuro” è forse una delle dediche più piene di significato che si possano fare e ricordo benissimo il momento in cui mi hai detto una cosa simile per la prima volta. Era Ottobre 2016, ci frequentavamo da un mesetto (e per la maggior parte del tempo di nascosto) ed eravamo a cena insieme. Ad un certo punto mi hai detto “dai vieni vicino a me”, mi hai abbracciato e mi hai sussurato “io non vedo l’ora di avere una famiglia con te” e questa frase mi ha colpita ed affondata: per me non c’è niente di più bello e sexy che vedere un uomo che è fiero di amare la propria persona e non veda l’ora di progettare un futuro insieme, senza paura. Questo è stato uno dei primi momenti in cui ho capito che probabilmente eri la mia persona ❤️ Con tutti i nostri casini, le centinaia di litigata, i mille difetti che abbiamo noi siamo noi, e non sceglierei mai nessun altro 🙏🏻

Yesterday we opened the #NespressoxChiaraFerragni Café in Milan and for the occasion we held a small conference to share with the journalists our mission 🙏
 @Anna.Lundstrom, @nespresso’s Chief Brand Officer, Stefano Goglio, Direttore Generale of @nespresso.it, my friend Annie Mazzola and I talked about the new #NespressoxChiaraFerragni limited edition collection we launched a few weeks ago, the shared values I have with Nespresso family like taking action, having a new and sustainable approach, using our voices to make a positive change and of course our love for coffee ☕ We also inaugurated the new benches in the piazza where the cafè is, it's our gift to the city of Milan ❤️ They are Nespresso’s and my way to express our commitment towards sustainability and this is only the first step of many 🙌 #adv

Dreams coming true 😍 My #NespressoxChiaraFerragni temporary cafè is open! You can find it in Piazza del Carmine in Milan from tomorrow until the 18th of July 📍 You can come here and have brunch, lunch, aperitivo and dinner or you can get a coffee-to-go with our personalized paper cups 💕
@Nespresso and I love coffee and ltaly’s heritage, that’s why we wanted to launch a cafè in the centre of Milan 💘 Also, along with @Nespresso.it family we created a new area with new benches and plants, right in front of the cafè, to make this piazza even more comfortable, this is part of our sustainable project and a gift to the city of Milan 🙏 #adv

Since so many are asking about it here is Leo’s birth story ❤️ We spent most of the pregnancy between Milan and Los Angeles and moved permanently to LA around my 29th week to be able to deliver Leo there. Until the 32nd week it was the easiest pregnancy ever: I was able to travel, work and do basically everything I used to do before. From week 32 I started having problems with my placenta. My liquids were also low and I was put at home rest with the idea to deliver max at 36 or 37 weeks. At 37 weeks my doc said it was safer not to wait any longer: at 1 am on March 19th I started induction at the hospital with a foley balloon and crazy (and super painful)  contractions. After I was a bit dialeted they took off the balloon and started oxytocin to prepare my body to deliver. A few hours later (at around 11 am) they broke my water (it’s like that during induction) and I requested my epidural (loved it). Everything was going smooth until Leo’s heartbeat started racing in the afternoon so the they had to give me oxygen, slow down the oxytocin and I started being very scared. At around 7 pm they told me I had an infection going on and gave me antibiotics. At this time I was super scared and thought they would opt for a C section (after 18 hours of labor) but then my doc came and I was dialeted enough to push and have a natural birth 😍 I pushed with Fede by my side and at 11.37 pm (22 hours after I started induction) I finally met my Leo. Best moment of my life so far. Polinesia 2019: our favorite trip as a couple. On Easter holidays 2019 we took 12 days to ourselves and flew all the way to Polinesia to finally enjoy a holiday we had postponed multiple times (first time we booked was when I found out I was pregnant with Leo in summer 2017 and the doctors suggested us not to go). We spent 5 days in Tetiaroa at The Brando (one of the best resorts I’ve ever stayed at) and 5 days in Bora Bora at The Four Seasons. The weather was a bit rainy at times but we had the time of our lives: swam with sharks, spent ours at the beach and explored the beautiful Polinesian culture 💖

Tokyo 💖 We were there for 10 amazing days in July 2019, while I was filming for @makingthecuttv. It was my third time in the city but the first time I actually had enough time to explore and really enjoy the amazing culture, and with my husband and son (who was one year and a half at the time) 🙏🏻 Hope to visit other parts of Japan soon!

2020: l’anno delle gioie e dei dolori, della paura e del coraggio, delle conquiste e delle perdite.
L’anno dell’ansia costante, della gratitudine per le piccole cose, della felicita’inaspettata. 
L’anno che mi ha fatto perdere la mia amata nonna Maria ad inizio pandemia ma che mi ha dato la forza per creare progetti che hanno aiutato altre persone in difficolta’. 
L’anno dei non viaggi, ma della scoperta della bellezza che e’nascosta nel nostro paese, nella nostra citta’ e nella nostra casa.
L’anno in cui mi e’sembrato di diventare grande, in cui sono stata fiera di prendere posizione ed in cui qualcosa dentro di me e’cambiato per sempre. 
L’anno in cui, più che mai, mi sono sentita fortunata per la salute della mia famiglia e per il mio lavoro che si e’evoluto ancora di più.
L’anno in cui, circondati da notizie di distruzione e morte, abbiamo deciso di creare una nuova vita, la nostra piccola speranza per il futuro. 
L’anno in cui ho capito quanto sia difficile vivere senza abbracci e senza vedere i sorrisi della gente. 
Non vedo l’ora di vivere il futuro a pieni polmoni, e della vittoria dell’umanita’contro questo maledetto virus, giorno in cui tutti noi potremo reiniziare la nostra rinascita 💖

2020: the year of joys and pains, of fears and courage, of achievement and loss.
The year of constant anxiety, of gratitude for the smallest things, of unexpected happiness.
The year that made me loose my beloved grandma Maria at the beginning of the pandemic but gave me the strenght to create powerful projects to help the community. 
The year of no travels, but of discovering the hidden beauty of my country, my city and my own home. 
The year in which I felt I grew up, in which I was proud to take a position and in which something inside me has changed forever.
The year that made me feel lucky for my family’s health and for my job which took new unexpected ways and always gave me purpose.
The year in which, surrounded by news of death and tragedies, we decided to create a new life, our little hope for the future.
The year that made me realize how hard it is to live without hugging people and watching their smiles.
I can’t wait to live the future breathing deeply
